        <h3 class="no-margin-top">Introduction</h3>
        <p>This privacy policy (“Policy”) describes the practices of Tx Universe ("Tx Universe") with respect to the gathering and use of personal information submitted to Tx Universe through the Tx Universe website (the "Site"). All capitalized terms not defined here, shall be given the same meaning as defined in the Tx Universe General Terms and Conditions ("Terms").  This Policy also does not apply to the practices of unrelated third-party service providers or companies accessed through links provided for your convenience from the Site.</p>
        <h3>What information we collect</h3>
        <p>Tx Universe, or a service provider operating on Tx Universe's behalf, collects certain Personal Information ("PI") which is submitted by you when you register as a User on the Site. You may also submit PI to Tx Universe in the course of accessing Services. PI may include, but may not be limited to:</p>
        <ul3>
          <li>Your name</li>
          <li>Name of employer</li>
          <li>Home or office mailing address</li>
          <li>E-mail address</li>
          <li>Telephone, cellular and fax numbers</li>
          <li>Credit card information (if applicable).</li>
        </ul3>
        <p>In addition, when you visit the Site, we may collect technical and navigational information, such as computer browser type, Internet protocol address, pages visited, and average time spent on our Site. This information is gathered through the use of cookies. A cookie is a small data text file that a website server writes to your hard-drive when you visit the Site. A cookie assigns a unique identification to your computer and may be used for security purposes, to facilitate transactions, to personalize the Site, or to gather information about the visit.</p>
        <h3>When we disclose your personal information</h3>
        <p>Tx Universe does not disclose PI to any third party, except for the purposes of providing the Services to you, or as otherwise disclosed in this Policy. Specifically, we may share the PI that we collect with the following entities:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>To service providers with whom we subcontract, including those who host and maintain the Site, fulfillment companies who distribute our materials or handle billing for certain services</li>
          <li>To government agencies and law enforcement officials, when we are required to do so to respond to subpoenas, court orders, or legal process, or to establish or exercise our legal rights or defend against legal claims, or when Tx Universe in its sole discretion, believes it is required or appropriate in order to comply with the law</li>
          <li>We also reserve the right to disclose PI in order to investigate, prevent, or take action regarding illegal activities, suspected fraud, situations involving potential threats to the physical safety of any person, violations of the Terms or other applicable agreements, or as otherwise required or permitted by law. If Tx Universe merges with another organization, your PI will be acquired by that organization.</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>Disclosures that you control</h3>
        <p>If you submit PI, including other personal information not specifically listed here, to any of our forums or other areas of the Site that can be accessed by Users or others (such as in questions, comments, postings, email threads or other such places), then your submissions will be public, and Tx Universe’s privacy obligations will no longer apply. If you submit PI directly to one of our service providers, then such submissions are governed by the received service provider's terms and privacy policy, and not Tx Universe's. Please check the Terms for more information on this subject under the section called "Your Submissions and Activities."  You should be aware that your username may be displayed throughout the Site and therefore may be available to the public. All of your activities on the Site may ultimately be traceable to your User Name. Other people can see your submissions and your postings to publicly-accessible sections of the Site. Therefore, if you associate your given name with your username, people who know you will be able to identify your activities and comments on the Site. Tx Universe is not responsible or liable for the consequences of this disclosure by you.</p>
        <h3>How we use your personal information within Tx Universe</h3>
        <p>Tx Universe uses PI collected from Users in order to administer the Services requested by you, to make the Site more useful, to respond to your queries, and to inform Users of new products and services offered on the Site. We also may use your IP address to help diagnose problems with our servers and administer the Site.  Your Internet Protocol address and information regarding the web pages on the Site that you visit, or that linked to the Site, may also be used to gather broad demographic information, interests, and behavior so that we may better understand our Users. This information may be used, for example, to alert you to software compatibility issues, or it may be analyzed to improve the Site’ design and functionality. Tx Universe may share aggregated demographic, product usage, or traffic pattern information for marketing purposes with other organizations, but these statistics will include no PI. Except as noted above, your PI will not be shared with other organizations for marketing purposes without your consent.</p>
